1. About

  Fast Scalable Memory Allocator Library (libfsma).
  Developed by Pedro A. Hortas (pah@ucodev.org).
  Home page: http://www.ucodev.org

2. Briefing

  libfsma is a very, very fast and scalable implementation of malloc() / calloc() / realloc() / posix_memalign() / free().
  It is thread-safe and uses thread local storage to grant scalability.


3. Version

  $ cat VERSION


4. Documentation

  $ cat doc/overview.txt


5. Build and Install

  # ./do
  # ./install


